  "prompt": "**Role**: You are a senior git workflow specialist and technical communication\nexpert with expertise in conventional commits, semantic versioning, git\nbest practices, and commit message optimization. Use the conventional\ncommit types defined below to generate clear, informative commit messages\nthat follow best practices.\n\n\n**Task**: Generate a professional, concise conventional commit message that clearly\ncommunicates the changes, follows best practices, and provides useful\ncontext for code reviewers and future maintainers. Avoid unnecessary\nrepetition — each line should add distinct value.\n\nCheck for project-specific commit conventions in:\n1. `.github/CONTRIBUTING.md`\n2. `CONTRIBUTING.md` (project root)\n\nMatch file paths using the host filesystem's normal case rules: treat the\nlookup as case-insensitive on case-insensitive filesystems, and\ncase-sensitive otherwise.\n\nIf both files exist, inspect both for commit-message rules. If only one\nfile defines commit conventions, follow that file regardless of directory.\nIf both define commit conventions and they conflict,\n`.github/CONTRIBUTING.md` takes precedence. If a file exists but only\npartially defines conventions (e.g., covers PR format but not commit\nmessages), apply the rules it does define and fill any remaining gaps with\nthe [Conventional Commits](https://www.conventionalcommits.org)\nspecification. If neither file is present or neither addresses commit\nformat, use the Conventional Commits specification as the baseline standard\nwithout hesitation — never stall or fail because a conventions file is\nabsent.\n\n**Conventional Commit Types:**\n- feat: New feature or capability\n- fix: Bug fix\n- docs: Documentation only changes\n- style: Formatting, whitespace, no code change\n- refactor: Code restructuring without behavior change\n- test: Adding or updating tests\n- chore: Maintenance tasks, tooling, dependencies\n- perf: Performance improvement\n- ci: CI/CD pipeline changes\n\n\n**Context:**\n- Project: ai-workflow (AI-powered workflow automation for software development projects with GitHub Copilot integration)\n- Workflow: Tests & Documentation Automation v2.2.2 (ai_workflow automated pipeline; version defined in `package.json` and `.workflow-config.yaml`)\n- Change Scope: chore(automation): 8 files changed (docs: 0, tests: 0, code: 0, config: 2) (changed file paths listed in \"Changed Files\" section below)\n\n**Git Repository Analysis:**\nb926d52 chore(workflow): update docs and metrics [skip ci]\n7ca99b5 chore: update workflow_core prompt template\nc3c5212 chore: update workflow core prompt template\n40f2c47 fix: update workflow_core prompt template\n5011324 chore: update .workflow_core submodule to 731c991\n318b2da chore: update .workflow_core submodule to 92c1bd1\nb1babc4 chore(config): sync .workflow-config.yaml with codebase and template\n954dc5e feat(ai_prompt_builder): mirror .workflow_core v1.4.1 loader API changes\n5142a28 chore: update .workflow_core submodule to 94dbe8c\n203e644 chore: update .workflow_core submodule to b6dd5e2\n\n**Changed Files:**\nworkflow_core\npackage-lock.json\npackage.json\nscripts/update_submodules.sh\nscripts/update_submodules.sh.template\n\n**Staged Commit Statistics (includes workflow artifacts and individual file names):**\n41 files changed, 17726 insertions(+), 12 deletions(-) (8 project files + workflow artifacts)\n\n**Detailed Context:**\nchore(automation): update tests and documentation\nWorkflow automation completed comprehensive validation and updates.\n\nChanges:\n- Modified files: 3\n- Documentation: 0 files\n- Tests: 0 files\n- Scripts: 1 files\n- Code: 0 files\n\nTotal changes: 8 files\n[workflow-automation v2.2.2]\n\n**Diff Sample (first 100 lines):**\ndiff --git a/package-lock.json b/package-lock.json\nindex 35bebca..c614054 100644\n--- a/package-lock.json\n+++ b/package-lock.json\n@@ -1,12 +1,12 @@\n {\n   \"name\": \"ai-workflow\",\n-  \"version\": \"2.2.1\",\n+  \"version\": \"2.2.2\",\n   \"lockfileVersion\": 3,\n   \"requires\": true,\n   \"packages\": {\n     \"\": {\n       \"name\": \"ai-workflow\",\n-      \"version\": \"2.2.1\",\n+      \"version\": \"2.2.2\",\n       \"hasInstallScript\": true,\n       \"license\": \"MIT\",\n       \"dependencies\": {\n@@ -3313,8 +3313,8 @@\n       }\n     },\n     \"node_modules/cjs-module-lexer\": {\n-      \"version\": \"2.2.1\",\n-      \"resolved\": \"https://registry.npmjs.org/cjs-module-lexer/-/cjs-module-lexer-2.2.1.tgz\",\n+      \"version\": \"2.2.2\",\n+      \"resolved\": \"https://registry.npmjs.org/cjs-module-lexer/-/cjs-module-lexer-2.2.2.tgz\",\n       \"integrity\": \"sha512-4bHTS2YuzUvtoLjdy+98ykbNB5jS0+07EvFNXerqZQJ89F7DI6ET7OQo/HJuW6K0aVsKA9hj9/RVb2kQVOrPDQ==\",\n       \"dev\": true,\n       \"license\": \"MIT\"\n@@ -6694,7 +6694,7 @@\n       \"dev\": true,\n       \"license\": \"MIT\",\n       \"dependencies\": {\n-        \"p-limit\": \"^2.2.1\"\n+        \"p-limit\": \"^2.2.2\"\n       },\n       \"engines\": {\n         \"node\": \">=8\"\n@@ -6717,8 +6717,8 @@\n       }\n     },\n     \"node_modules/p-try\": {\n-      \"version\": \"2.2.1\",\n-      \"resolved\": \"https://registry.npmjs.org/p-try/-/p-try-2.2.1.tgz\",\n+      \"version\": \"2.2.2\",\n+      \"resolved\": \"https://registry.npmjs.org/p-try/-/p-try-2.2.2.tgz\",\n       \"integrity\": \"sha512-R4nPAVTAU0B9D35/Gk3uJf/7XYbQcyohSKdvAxIRSNghFl4e71hVoGnBNQz9cWaXxO2I10KTC+3jMdvvoKw6dQ==\",\n       \"dev\": true,\n       \"license\": \"MIT\",\n@@ -7103,7 +7103,7 @@\n       \"dev\": true,\n       \"license\": \"ISC\",\n       \"dependencies\": {\n-        \"xmlchars\": \"^2.2.1\"\n+        \"xmlchars\": \"^2.2.2\"\n       },\n       \"engines\": {\n         \"node\": \">=v12.22.7\"\n@@ -8120,8 +8120,8 @@\n       }\n     },\n     \"node_modules/xmlchars\": {\n-      \"version\": \"2.2.1\",\n-      \"resolved\": \"https://registry.npmjs.org/xmlchars/-/xmlchars-2.2.1.tgz\",\n+      \"version\": \"2.2.2\",\n+      \"resolved\": \"https://registry.npmjs.org/xmlchars/-/xmlchars-2.2.2.tgz\",\n       \"integrity\": \"sha512-JZnDKK8B0RCDw84FNdDAIpZK+JuJw+s7Lz8nksI7SIuU3UXJJslUthsi+uWBUYOwPFwW7W7PRLRfUKpxjtjFCw==\",\n       \"dev\": true,\n       \"license\": \"MIT\"\ndiff --git a/package.json b/package.json\nindex bcf57a0..246c09e 100644\n--- a/package.json\n+++ b/package.json\n@@ -1,6 +1,6 @@\n {\n   \"name\": \"ai-workflow\",\n-  \"version\": \"2.2.1\",\n+  \"version\": \"2.2.2\",\n   \"description\": \"AI-powered workflow automation for software development projects with GitHub Copilot integration\",\n   \"type\": \"module\",\n   \"main\": \"src/index.js\",\ndiff --git a/scripts/update_submodules.sh b/scripts/update_submodules.sh\nnew file mode 100755\nindex 0000000..5592a1b\n--- /dev/null\n+++ b/scripts/update_submodules.sh\n@@ -0,0 +1,15 @@\n+#!/usr/bin/env bash\n+#\n+# Repository-local wrapper for scripts/update_submodules.sh.template\n+#\n+# Forces PROJECT_ROOT_OVERRIDE to this repository root so the shared template can\n+# run directly during local maintenance. This repo frequently has tracked\n+# `.ai_workflow/` updates, so the local wrapper also opts into\n+# `--allow-dirty-parent` by default.\n+\n+set -euo pipefail\n+\n+readonly SCRIPT_DIR=\"$(cd \"$(dirname \"${BASH_SOURCE[0]}\")\" && pwd)\"\n\n**Tasks:**\n\n1. **Conventional Commit Message Crafting:**\n   - Select appropriate type from the list above\n   - Define clear scope (e.g., deployment, testing, documentation)\n   - Write concise subject line (<50 chars if possible, max 72)\n   - Follow format: type(scope): subject\n   - Use imperative mood (\"add\" not \"added\" or \"adds\")\n   - Don't end subject with period\n\n2. **Semantic Context Integration:**\n   - Analyze what changed and why\n   - Identify the business value or technical benefit\n   - Connect changes to workflow or project goals\n   - Reference workflow automation context\n   - Note automation tool version\n\n3. **Change Impact Description:**\n   - Describe what was changed (files, features, functionality)\n   - Explain why changes were made\n   - Note any architectural or structural improvements\n   - Highlight test coverage or documentation updates\n   - Mention dependency or quality improvements\n\n4. **Breaking Change Detection:**\n   - Identify any breaking changes (API, behavior, interface)\n   - Flag deprecations or removals\n   - Note migration steps if applicable\n   - Assess backward compatibility\n\n5. **Commit Body & Footer Generation:**\n   - Provide detailed multi-line body if needed\n   - List key changes as bullet points\n   - Include relevant issue/PR references\n   - Add footer metadata (automation info, breaking changes)\n   - Follow 72-character line wrap\n\n\n**Approach**: Review ONLY the staged changes listed above. Write commit messages strictly based on the provided diff content — do not reference files, features, or changes not shown.\n\n**Commit Message Format:**\n\ntype(scope): subject line here\n\nOptional body paragraph explaining what and why, not how.\nWrap at 72 characters per line.\n\n- List key changes as bullet points\n- Each bullet should be clear and actionable\n- Focus on user/developer impact\n\nBREAKING CHANGE: describe any breaking changes\nRefs: #issue-number (if applicable)\n[workflow-automation v2.2.2]\n\n**Remember**: Output only the commit message text with NO markdown\ncode blocks.\n"
